<paragraph blockId="26.[189,1399,1318,1486]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[189,436,1319,1344]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cosanga" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,436,1319,1344]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Mesoconius cosanga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[444,536,1319,1345]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is very closely related to the Colombian species 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[1123,1291,1319,1345]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albitergum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1123,1291,1319,1345]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">M. albitergum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1300,1394,1319,1345]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, with which it shares the distinctive desclerotization of the middle abdominal segments. It differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[189,358,1389,1415]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albitergum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,358,1389,1415]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">M. albitergum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[367,460,1390,1416]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in having white fore tarsi, a pale anterior spiracle and a mostly orange notum without broad black vittae. 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[512,758,1425,1450]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cosanga" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[512,758,1425,1450]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Mesoconius cosanga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[765,856,1425,1451]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[913,1081,1424,1450]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albitergum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[913,1081,1424,1450]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">M. albitergum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1088,1179,1425,1451]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
were recovered as a single branch on the CO1 tree, but with a deep split between the species.
</paragraph>
